---
description: Use when changing API behavior, schemas, configs, persisted data, or public interfaces where compatibility may be affected.
alwaysApply: false
---

Preserve existing behavior and interfaces by default.

- Do not introduce breaking changes without explicit user approval.
- If a breaking change is required, clearly mark it and provide migration or rollout steps.
- Avoid silent behavior changes; call out intentional behavior differences.
- For data/schema/config changes, include rollback or recovery considerations when applicable.
